# Goose hints for Actor Coach PWA

## Project overview
Pure frontend Next.js 14 PWA. 3 screens: Roulette → Record → Feedback. All state in sessionStorage. No backend, no database, no API routes, no middleware.

## Golden rules
- NEVER create API routes, middleware, server stores, or session management
- NEVER add Redis, Docker, or any server-side dependencies
- ALL logic goes in the client — components, libs, and pages
- ALL state uses sessionStorage (not cookies, not server stores)
- Keep it simple — this is an MVP

## File structure
src/
  app/                  # Next.js App Router pages
    page.tsx            # Auto-redirects to /roulette
    roulette/page.tsx   # Spin wheel, start take
    record/page.tsx     # Submit take, call AI stub
    feedback/page.tsx   # Show scores + deltas
  components/           # React components
  lib/                  # Pure client libraries
  types/                # All TypeScript types

## Key conventions
- All interactive pages use 'use client'
- Styling uses Tailwind with custom theme: stage-*, crimson-*, gold-*, electric-*
- Animations respect prefers-reduced-motion
- EMOTIONS array has exactly 20 entries (defined in types/index.ts)
- FALLBACK_LINES has exactly 50 entries (defined in fallbackPool.ts)
- analyzeTake() in ai.ts returns mock data — replace body only, keep signature
- validateLine() checks for forbidden content — keep regex list updated
- SW is at public/sw.js — caches _next/static/* and icons, network-first for pages
- Manifest at public/manifest.json — SVG icons only
- Register SW via inline script in layout.tsx

## Tests
- tests/unit/ for pure logic (validation, fallbackPool, types)
- tests/component/ for component rendering
- tests/ setup.ts has MediaRecorder + getUserMedia mocks
- Jest config is jest.config.js (not .ts)
- Run: npm test

## Package.json rules
- No server dependencies (no ioredis, no iron-session, no jose, no fluent-ffmpeg)
- Next.js output: standalone
- Keep dependency count minimal

## When adding features
1. Add types first (src/types/index.ts)
2. Add lib functions if needed
3. Add/update component
4. Update page
5. Add test
6. Verify with npm test + npm run build
